### Smart Shelf Testing - HTTP Requests
### Use with REST Client VSCode extension or copy to Postman

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Create Shelf Location A1
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shelfCode": "A1",
  "shelfName": "Main Pharmacy Shelf A",
  "row": "1",
  "column": "A",
  "zone": "General",
  "capacity": 50,
  "qrCode": "QR-SHELF-A1",
  "notes": "First test shelf"
}

### 2. Create Shelf Location B2 (Refrigerated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shelfCode": "B2",
  "shelfName": "Refrigerated Shelf B",
  "row": "2",
  "column": "B",
  "zone": "Refrigerated",
  "capacity": 30,
  "qrCode": "QR-SHELF-B2",
  "notes": "Cold storage shelf"
}

### 3. Create Shelf Location C3 (Controlled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shelfCode": "C3",
  "shelfName": "Controlled Substances Shelf",
  "row": "3",
  "column": "C",
  "zone": "Controlled",
  "capacity": 100,
  "qrCode": "QR-SHELF-C3",
  "notes": "Locked cabinet for controlled meds"
}

### 4. Get All Shelves
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get Shelf by ID (replace {shelfId})
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get Smart Shelf Analytics
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/analytics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Add Batch to Shelf (replace {shelfId} and {batchId})
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}/batch/{batchId}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Get Shelf Queue (replace {shelfId})
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}/queue
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Validate Batch Pick - CORRECT pick (replace {shelfId} and {batchId})
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}/validate-pick
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchId": "{batchId-at-position-0}"
}

### 10. Validate Batch Pick - INCORRECT pick (replace {shelfId} and {batchId})
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}/validate-pick
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchId": "{batchId-not-at-position-0}"
}

### 11. Get Unacknowledged Alerts
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/alerts/unacknowledged?limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 12. Acknowledge Alert (replace {alertId})
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/alerts/{alertId}/acknowledge
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13. Get Expiring Batches (30 days)
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/expiring?days=30&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 14. Record Expiry Action - Return to Vendor (replace {batchId})
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/expiry-action
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchId": "{batchId}",
  "action": "RETURN_TO_VENDOR",
  "quantity": 100,
  "vendorReturn": true,
  "reason": "Expiring soon, vendor accepts returns",
  "notes": "Contacted vendor XYZ"
}

### 15. Record Expiry Action - Discount (replace {batchId})
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/expiry-action
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchId": "{batchId}",
  "action": "DISCOUNT",
  "quantity": 50,
  "vendorReturn": false,
  "discountAmount": 25.00,
  "reason": "Apply 25% discount to clear stock",
  "notes": "Promotional sale"
}

### 16. Record Expiry Action - Dispose (replace {batchId})
POST {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/expiry-action
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchId": "{batchId}",
  "action": "DISPOSE",
  "quantity": 20,
  "vendorReturn": false,
  "reason": "Expired and damaged",
  "notes": "Disposed according to regulations"
}

### 17. Get Expiry Action History
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/expiry-actions?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 18. Get Expiry Actions for Specific Batch (replace {batchId})
GET {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/expiry-actions?batchId={batchId}&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 19. Remove Batch from Front of Queue (replace {shelfId})
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}/batch/front
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 20. Update Shelf (replace {shelfId})
PUT {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shelfName": "Updated Shelf Name",
  "capacity": 75,
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "notes": "Updated notes"
}

### 21. Delete Shelf (replace {shelfId} - only works if no batches)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/smart-shelf/{shelfId}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ===== HELPER REQUESTS =====

### Get All Inventory Batches (to find batch IDs)
GET {{baseUrl}}/inventory?page=1&limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Drugs (to create batches)
GET {{baseUrl}}/drugs?page=1&limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Suppliers (to create batches)
GET {{baseUrl}}/suppliers?page=1&limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create Test Batch (Expiring Soon) - replace drugId and supplierId
POST {{baseUrl}}/inventory
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "drugId": "{drugId}",
  "batchNumber": "TEST-BATCH-001",
  "quantity": 100,
  "purchasePrice": 50,
  "sellPrice": 100,
  "expiryDate": "2025-01-05",
  "supplierId": "{supplierId}",
  "location": "Warehouse A"
}
